      "id": "PopularPost315390",
      "post_content": "Questions how does this work with split cards and fuse splits?   \n  \n1st, split cards with fuse I can't find a ruling. I know on split cards you can cast only 1 side without paying it's mana cost. I'm only assuming you can't fuse the spells because it would be like paying a kicker or similar?   \n*Answer I found - If you\u2019re casting a split card with fuse from any zone other than your hand, you can\u2019t cast both halves. You\u2019ll only be able to cast one half or the other.*  \n  \n2nd, I need confirmation on this ruling: \"If the copied card is a split card, you may choose to cast either side of the split card, but not both. The split cards Fire/Ice, Illusion/Reality, Night/Day, Stand/Deliver, and Wax/Wane all have at least one side with converted mana cost 2 or less.\"  \n  \nTo me you can choose what side you are casting upon activation not that you are only coping one side and can only cast that side since it doesn't say copy only cast in the ruling. I have a judge telling me I can only copy... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Tower_Mazer",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost315390\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">Questions how does this work with split cards and fuse splits?  <br/><br/>1st, split cards with fuse I can't find a ruling.  I know on split cards you can cast only 1 side without paying it's mana cost.  I'm only assuming you can't fuse the spells because it would be like paying a kicker or similar?  <br/><i><u>Answer I found - If you\u2019re casting a split card with fuse from any zone other than your hand, you can\u2019t cast both halves. You\u2019ll only be able to cast one half or the other.</u></i><br/><br/>2nd, I need confirmation on this ruling:  \"If the copied card is a split card, you may choose to cast either side of the split card, but not both. The split cards Fire/Ice, Illusion/Reality, Night/Day, Stand/Deliver, and Wax/Wane all have at least one side with converted mana cost 2 or less.\"<br/><br/>To me you can choose what side you are casting upon activation not that you are only coping one side and can only cast that side since it doesn't say copy only cast in the ruling.  I have a judge telling me I can only copy... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 315390)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '315390'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                