      "id": "PopularPost287238",
      "post_content": "@Toquinha1977: You can only Cipher the spell card itself, not a copy, as the rules for Cipher specifically state that you may exile \"this spell card\". A spell cast through Isochron Scepter (or, for that matter, through Cipher itself) is not a card, so you cannot Cipher it.  \n  \n@HoboColin: \"Alternative cost\" means something like [Force of Will](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Force of Will) where you do something else instead of pay its usual cost. You can't do that with scepter. \"Additional cost\" is something like [Fling](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling) where you have to do something else in addition to its usual cost. You CAN put Fling on this but you'd have to sac a creature every time you use it. Kicker is an optional additional cost. You are never forced to pay the Kicker, but you have the option to. If you choose to Kick the spell then you have to pay the kicker cost.  \n  \n@Tower\\_Mazer: First, you can't use Fuse with Isochron Scepter. Fuse is an alternative cost, like buyback. Second, in every case where you imprint a split car... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "adrian.malacoda",
